From: receiver-android (Basecamp) — embedding liblogosdelivery via FFI on Android
Subject: [PATCH] ffi_context: guard empty/nil event payloads in callEventCallback

`callEventCallback` passes `unsafeAddr event[0]` (and `unsafeAddr msg[0]` in the
except branch) to the C `FFICallBack`. For an empty Nim string the seq/string
data pointer is nil, so `event[0]` dereferences nil ->
`SIGSEGV: Illegal storage access. (Attempt to read from nil?)`.

This fires the first time the node emits an event that serializes to an empty
string. Guard both call sites: pass `nil` (with len 0) instead of indexing an
empty string.

Applies to the released 0.1.x line (v0.1.3 / v0.1.4 / v0.1.5), where the
template lives in `ffi/ffi_context.nim`. The line numbers below match v0.1.3
(the revision pinned by logos-delivery). See the accompanying report for the
master-branch status.

diff --git a/ffi/ffi_context.nim b/ffi/ffi_context.nim
--- a/ffi/ffi_context.nim
+++ b/ffi/ffi_context.nim
@@ -36,7 +36,9 @@ template callEventCallback*(ctx: ptr FFIContext, eventName: string, body: untyped
     try:
       let event = body
       cast[FFICallBack](ctx[].eventCallback)(
-        RET_OK, unsafeAddr event[0], cast[csize_t](len(event)), ctx[].eventUserData
+        RET_OK,
+        (if len(event) > 0: unsafeAddr event[0] else: nil),
+        cast[csize_t](len(event)), ctx[].eventUserData
       )
     except Exception, CatchableError:
       let msg =
@@ -43,5 +43,7 @@ template callEventCallback*(ctx: ptr FFIContext, eventName: string, body: untyped
         "Exception " & eventName & " when calling 'eventCallBack': " &
         getCurrentExceptionMsg()
       cast[FFICallBack](ctx[].eventCallback)(
-        RET_ERR, unsafeAddr msg[0], cast[csize_t](len(msg)), ctx[].eventUserData
+        RET_ERR,
+        (if len(msg) > 0: unsafeAddr msg[0] else: nil),
+        cast[csize_t](len(msg)), ctx[].eventUserData
       )
